The paper deals with downlink precoding for physical layer multicasting in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers channel estimation, pilot contamination, and multi-group multicasting, which are topics related to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on the design of multicasting schemes, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM).
